transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi. Thank you for calling Viagra at ScoreBlue. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir. First of all, I need to cancel my prescription.

Speaker 1: And I went online, and I was trying to get the newest Viagra.

Speaker 2: And once I put my information, my debit card number,

Speaker 1: it automatically charged me for a prescription I used to have.

Speaker 2: And I didn't know how to stop it or anything,

Speaker 1: so you guys charged me $113 for a prescription that I did not want.

Speaker 2: Sure. Let's get this fixed for you.

Speaker 1: Excuse me?

Speaker 2: Yeah, we can get this fixed for you.

Speaker 1: You want to make sure you – yeah, so you wanted the AGV.

Speaker 2: You did not want the previous prescription of Viagra,

Speaker 1: and you want me to cancel the previous and get you the proper medication, correct?

Speaker 2: Well, I wanted a one-time deal. I didn't want a prescription.

Speaker 1: And I didn't know how to just get – excuse me?

Speaker 2: These are prescriptions, especially AGV.

Speaker 1: So when a doctor writes it for you, it will come with refills.

Speaker 2: I don't normally recommend canceling right away because the doctors don't like that.

Speaker 1: Because hypothetically, if you get that first prescription,

Speaker 2: and you like it, and you cancel it before you want a refill,

Speaker 1: they won't write you another prescription, at least through Score Blue.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Because they'd rather not have a patient do that.

Speaker 2: But we can pause it where you won't have reoccurring shipments until you want one.

Speaker 1: Well, no, I don't even – because I got five prescriptions

Speaker 2: that I haven't used for one pill out of the five prescriptions.

Speaker 1: And once I realized – that's why I canceled prescription at first.

Speaker 2: Sure.

Speaker 1: So I apologize to cut you off,

Speaker 2: but this would be a lot easier if I could look up your account

Speaker 1: and make adjustments and see what we're talking about.

Speaker 2: Can I get your full name and date of birth?

Speaker 1: Michael Carter, birthday 9-4-65, 1965.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: So Mr. Carter, I'm looking at your script right here.

Speaker 2: It was written back in July.

Speaker 1: And this was for a quantity of 25 of the 50-milligram Viagra.

Speaker 2: The doctor had written it with five monthly refills.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: So I did see one went through on the 27th.

Speaker 2: Now, what I'm going to do right now – because you mentioned you don't want that.

Speaker 1: I'm going to attempt to cancel it with the pharmacy.

Speaker 2: So I'm going to reach out to the pharmacy right now.

Speaker 1: Once they confirm cancellation on this most recent one,

Speaker 2: I'll be able to issue a refund of the $113.95, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Or what I can do for you is switch that over to the AGV like you wanted.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Is that the newest one?

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: So I could get you – because of this inconvenience,

Speaker 1: I could get you 25 100-milligram Viagra AGV,

Speaker 2: and I can honor that price of the $113.95 that you paid for the generics.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: After that, I want to pause.

Speaker 2: Correct.

Speaker 1: So, yeah, what we can do is we can then pause it.

Speaker 2: So then that gives you time to try the new medication, see how you like it,

Speaker 1: and then you can let us know how you want to proceed.

Speaker 2: But the thing about it on that pause, once I realize I want it,

Speaker 1: I'm going to have to give you another card.

Speaker 2: I mean, I'm going to have to get another card because I canceled my card.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Because I can't afford to keep getting charged for something I don't want.

Speaker 1: Sure.

Speaker 2: Yeah, you don't need – yeah, you can always call us

Speaker 1: and add that information later down the road.

Speaker 2: Bear with me right here where I'm going to adjust these prescriptions really fast.

Speaker 1: Okay?

Speaker 2: Give me one moment.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So I went ahead and made those adjustments, okay?

Speaker 1: So I canceled the incorrect order, replaced that with the proper medication.

Speaker 2: I'm honoring your previous price of what you paid for of the $113.95,

Speaker 1: and I am going to put your account on that pause, okay?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: So is this the one that it works in 15 minutes?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Hello?

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: I'm right here.

Speaker 1: I'm just making notes under the account for the pharmacy.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right, Michael.

Speaker 2: You're all set.

Speaker 1: That's been done and completed.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: You're very welcome.

Speaker 1: Anything else I can help you with today?

Speaker 2: No, that's it.

Speaker 1: All righty.

Speaker 2: You have a lovely rest of your day.

Speaker 1: Feel free to give us a call back in the future with any questions.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye.
